  overviewText="A custom sports mouthguard is fabricated from a precise model of your teeth and fits snugly around every surface — which is what makes it effective. When an impact occurs, a properly fitting guard distributes the force across the entire arch, cushions the jaw from being snapped shut, and protects the lips and cheeks from the teeth. Generic boil-and-bite guards don't fit closely enough to accomplish this reliably, which is why sports medicine research consistently shows custom guards provide significantly better protection than OTC alternatives."
  overviewExtra="Young athletes throughout Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck play football, basketball, soccer, hockey, lacrosse, and martial arts — all sports that carry real dental injury risk. At Thrive Dental, we fabricate custom mouthguards for athletes of all ages in a range of thicknesses and materials depending on the sport and contact level. We can also incorporate team colors, which younger athletes particularly appreciate. A custom mouthguard from our Bayside practice typically costs less than a single dental crown — and it prevents the kind of injuries that lead to crowns, implants, and months of restorative treatment. If your child plays a contact sport without a properly fitting guard, call us."
